This is not a rehearsal.

14:55.103 --> 14:56.598
 You ready? You ready?
- Yes. Yes.

14:56.688 --> 14:57.851
Okay.

14:57.940 --> 15:01.309
Come in, if you dare.

15:03.403 --> 15:06.357
- Dad.
 Huh? Oh. Let me see...

15:06.448 --> 15:09.200
Thank you for joining us on our...

15:09.284 --> 15:11.076
No, no, no.
First the thunder and the lightning.

15:11.161 --> 15:13.035
Yeah, right. I got it.

15:13.121 --> 15:14.201
Perfect.

15:14.289 --> 15:18.536
Thank you for joining us
on our special night.

15:18.627 --> 15:22.043
Other children haven't fared so well.

15:22.130 --> 15:25.665
  Welcome to your nightmare.
Ha, ha, ha, ha.

15:26.426 --> 15:27.885
What the hell is that?

15:27.970 --> 15:29.547
Can we just get our candy?

15:29.638 --> 15:35.059
Okay, but beware of the fog,
for you might not be able to see ahead.

15:37.145 --> 15:39.387
Timmy starting running.
I wanted to run too...

15:39.481 --> 15:42.233
but my hunch got stuck
on a rosebush, and that's when I fell.

15:42.317 --> 15:43.432
I fell hard.

15:43.527 --> 15:45.021
I can see his feet.

15:45.112 --> 15:48.445
Okay, here.
Here, children, have some candy.

15:48.532 --> 15:50.489
Happy Halloween.

15:53.495 --> 15:55.618
Okay, that was bad. That was a bad start.

15:55.706 --> 15:59.573
Uh, first of all, Dad,
thunder, lightning, fog cue...

15:59.668 --> 16:01.162
And we skipped Alex altogether.

16:01.253 --> 16:04.207
And Gloria, since when
do you speak English?

16:04.298 --> 16:08.592
Oh, so now you have
a problem with the way I speak?

16:08.677 --> 16:12.378
Like father, like daughter
in this dog-eat-dog family.

16:14.016 --> 16:16.589
Okay, places! Places!
Good. Mitchell's good.

16:16.685 --> 16:18.263
Honey, I love you so much...

16:18.353 --> 16:20.311
Not now. Not now.

16:20.397 --> 16:23.398
Come in, if you dare.

16:24.193 --> 16:25.603
- Dad.
 What?

16:25.694 --> 16:27.521
- Dad!
