me and that's when I wet my pants!

17:01.563 --> 17:04.233
I wet my pants! I wet my pants.

17:05.317 --> 17:07.144
- This place is weird.
- Yeah.

17:07.236 --> 17:08.730
- Let's go.
- Yeah, come on.

17:12.324 --> 17:15.194
- Son of a...
- What is wrong with everyone?

17:15.285 --> 17:16.944
Cam, "townspeople"? Really?

17:17.037 --> 17:18.531
I lived on a farm. They lived in town.

17:18.622 --> 17:20.116
They <i>were</i> the townspeople.

17:20.207 --> 17:24.417
And Dad...
Dad, it goes lightning, thunder, fog cue.

17:24.502 --> 17:27.076
This whole thing is a colossal fog cue.

17:27.172 --> 17:29.924
Claire just doesn't understand, Cam.

17:30.008 --> 17:33.923
Maybe she's never been picked on
for been different.

17:34.012 --> 17:35.672
When, Gloria?

17:35.764 --> 17:39.180
When have you ever been picked on
for "been different"?

17:39.268 --> 17:41.509
Ask the gargle.

17:41.603 --> 17:43.263
What is she saying?

17:44.356 --> 17:45.387
Gloria!

17:46.733 --> 17:49.485
 Think she went insane.
- She's not insane!

17:49.570 --> 17:52.487
- She's my mother.
- I'm your mother now!

17:53.866 --> 17:56.866
Gloria, I wanna tell you a story...

17:56.952 --> 17:58.861
about a guy eating in a diner, alone.

17:58.954 --> 18:02.240
Behind him he hears a woman talking.
He doesn't turn around.

18:02.332 --> 18:07.290
Five minutes, 10 minutes, just listening
for the woman, the life in her voice.

18:07.379 --> 18:11.080
And before he even sees her,
he realizes he's fallen in love.

18:11.175 --> 18:13.333
Now I give you a guess who that guy is.

18:17.097 --> 18:18.046
Oh, my dad was...

18:20.309 --> 18:23.512
- You know what? I'm just gonna go.
- No. Come on, Cam.

18:23.604 --> 18:26.355
Uh, if Uncle Cam's leaving,
I'm just gonna go upstairs and study.

18:26.440 --> 18:28.895
Yeah, I have a party to go to, so...

18:28.984 --> 18:31.142
